<p>So I made a Acces Point on the raspberry pi. But for a school project I need to connect to it with my phone without it being connected to ethernet.</p>  <p>I tried to remove the bridging part but then I can't connect to the pi.</p>  <p>I'm using HostAPD.</p>  <p>network interfaces:</p>  <p><div class="snippet" data-lang="js" data-hide="false"> <div class="snippet-code"> <pre class="snippet-code-html lang-html prettyprint-override"><code>#wpa-conf /etc/wpa_supplicant/wpa_supplicant.conf  auto wlan1 allow-hotplug wlan1 iface wlan1 inet manual wpa-conf /etc/wpa_supplicant/wpa_supplicant.conf  auto br0 iface br0 inet dhcp bridge_ports eth0 wlan0</code></pre> </div> </div> </p>  <p>hostapd</p>  <p><div class="snippet" data-lang="js" data-hide="false"> <div class="snippet-code"> <pre class="snippet-code-html lang-html prettyprint-override"><code>interface=wlan0 driver=rtl871xdrv bridge=br0 ssid=ProfielWerkstuk channel=1 wmm_enabled=0 wpa=3 wpa_passphrase=pass wpa_key_mgmt=WPA-PSK wpa_pairwise=TKIP rsn_pairwise=CCMP auth_algs=1 macaddr_acl=0</code></pre> </div> </div> </p>  <p>Somebody know how to achieve this?</p>